title: Omani sailor lost at sea
text:
PARIS — Coastguards have launched a search for an Omani sailor lost at sea off the coast of Croatia after falling overboard Wednesday, his Musandam-Oman Sail team announced.
The captain of the Oman-based multihull boat, Frenchman Sidney Gavignet, raised the alarm at 0305 GMT after Mohammed Al Alawi fell overboard.
Croatian and Italian coastguards were assisting with the search-and-rescue operation for Al-Alawi, who was part of a five-man crew heading to Trieste in Italy to take part in the Barcolana international sailing regatta. — AFP
